&lt;p&gt;Household energy consumption and climate change are highly related. On the one hand, residential energy sector has become a major energy consumption sector, responsible for significant emissions of carbon dioxide (CO2) (Mi et al., 2020). According to the International Energy Agency (IEA) data, residents consumed 21% of global total final energy in 2019 (IEA, 2022). On the other hand, climate change has impacts on household energy consumption. Global temperature rise will increase energy demand for cooling and decrease energy demand for heating. In addition, household energy consumption is known to affect human well-being and can result in harmful environmental impacts. Thus, understanding the changes and dynamics of household energy consumption as well as the associated greenhouse gas emission and environmental impacts at the global and regional level will be critical for achieving climate change mitigation targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guest editors:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prof. Dr. Zhifu Mi, PhD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University College London, London, UK&lt;br&gt;(Climate change economics, energy policy, carbon neutrality)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Lu Jiang, PhD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beijing Normal University, Beijing, China&lt;br&gt;(Energy geography, regional sustainability, energy consumption)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent work has identified several critical factors that affect the consumption of household energy, including household characteristics, energy prices, and energy-related policies (Wolske et al., 2020; Wu et al., 2017; Zhou et al., 2016). Therefore, the type and amount of household energy consumption are different within and across regions and nations. In the coming years, household energy transition requires further development to achieve policy objectives and function well in climate change mitigation (Mi et al., 2020).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The special issue “Household energy consumption and climate change” aims to improve understanding on the regional diversity and effects of relevance to energy consumption in our households. This issue will provide a platform for cross-cutting analyses that inform global, national and regional climate change mitigation targets. It will provide critical advices for key stakeholders such as policy makers, practitioner, industries and households. Hence, we invite submissions on the following topics:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Household energy use and environmental impacts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Residential mobility, space heating, and cooling energy demand&lt;br&gt;- Ecology and climate consequences of energy use&lt;br&gt;- Environmental impacts of energy use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Household energy efficiency and energy conservation&lt;br&gt;- Household energy consumption behaviors&lt;br&gt;- The rebound effect on energy efficiency&lt;br&gt;- Technology innovation and household energy consumption&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. Energy poverty and energy justice&lt;br&gt;- Definitions and methodological aspects of energy poverty&lt;br&gt;- The relationship between energy poverty, poverty and inequality&lt;br&gt;- Energy inequity and health risk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4. Household energy consumption and climate change governance&lt;br&gt;- Energy transition and renewable energy&lt;br&gt;- Urbanization and household energy consumption&lt;br&gt;- Household energy consumption and climate change management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5. Household energy demand in a warming world&lt;br&gt;- Impacts of global warming on household heating and cooling energy&lt;br&gt;- Forecasting of household energy demand&lt;br&gt;- Structural upgrading of household energy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manuscript submission information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are invited to submit your manuscript at any time before the submission deadline of &lt;strong&gt;July 31, 2023&lt;/strong&gt;. For any inquiries about the appropriateness of contribution topics, please contact Executive Guest Editor &lt;strong&gt;Zhifu Mi &lt;/strong&gt;via z.mi@ucl.ac.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The journal’s submission platform (&lt;a href="https://www.editorialmanager.com/jepo/default2.aspx"&gt;Editorial Manager®&lt;/a&gt;) is available for receiving submissions to this Special Issue. Please refer to the &lt;a href="https://www.elsevier.com/journals/energy-policy/0301-4215/guide-for-authors"&gt;Guide for Authors&lt;/a&gt; to prepare your manuscript. When submitting your manuscripts, please choose "&lt;strong&gt;VSI: Household energy&lt;/strong&gt;" from the dropdown menu.&lt;/p&gt;
