&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current environmental and societal sustainability issues and challenges of GHG reduction, toxic and particulates pollution, water use minimisation, wastewater treatment, recycling and reuse of material and energy remain extremely complex, highly interactive and strongly interdependent. The mitigation measures and actions, therefore, require holistic approaches and sound methods for implementable solutions. The current world situation is volatile due to various factors as the post-COVID recovery, fragile economies and conflicts. The 26th conference “Process Integration, Modelling and Optimisation for Energy Saving and Pollution Reduction” – PRES’23, held in Thessaloniki, Greece, 8-11 October 2023, provides a platform for discussing ideas and developing solutions for cleaner processes. Holistic approaches from the family of Process Integration employing systematic optimisation based on rigorous and simplified models enable increased process performance at the best possible efficiency of material and energy utilisation, enabling win-win solutions that minimise environmental impacts at improved economic performance.&lt;/p&gt;
