&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interest for researchers, practitioners, and the readership of JCLP and CLSCN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;This issue expects to deliver timely investigations that can assist practitioners, policymakers, and researchers to draw a pathway to involve consumers in returning EOL products, envisioning circular systems. Consumers have a special part in the operationalization of circular supply chains; hence, this issue should provide knowledge and opportunities for increasing EOL product return rates, in alignment with the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals. All received manuscripts must explicitly describe how the research outcomes contribute to the 17 United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDG).&lt;/p&gt;
