&lt;p&gt;This special issue focuses on urban technologies, digitalization, innovations, and solutions related to all dimensions of sustainability. United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) indicate broad definition of sustainability and we welcome papers related to one or more these goals and definitions of sustainable development. Suitable topics include e.g. studies on digitalization (e.g. AI, Open Data, Big Data, Urban Analytics), urban development technologies, technology clusters, and green innovations in cities. The theme issue welcomes article proposals that will provide insight to spatial formations of information, communication, technologies and knowledge production from the various perspectives including analyses public and private sectors together with NGOs and other stakeholders. Potential papers may focus on theoretical developments or empirical analyses. The articles are targeted to academic community as well as practitioners, such as spatial developers, planners and officers in order to increase understanding of the dynamics and factors effecting urban form, structure, and spatiality. Analytical contributions to the challenges and obstacles in decision making in major cities or/and smaller ones are warmly welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sustainable Urban Technology refers to the development and application of innovative technologies that enable cities to operate in an environmentally sustainable and socially responsible manner. These technologies focus on improving the efficiency and effectiveness of urban infrastructure, including transportation systems, water and waste management, energy consumption, and building design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable topics include but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integration of spatial analysis and technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regional case studies of technology geographies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Epistemological considerations of data, information, and knowledge in spatial or urban development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spatial scaling of knowledge sources for economic growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technology clusters and knowledge insensitivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intra-urban dichotomies and digitalization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Case based solutions for urban development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparative studies of innovative growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local lessons of science/technology&amp;/innovation initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Policy studies of technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travelling theory, location context and technology domains&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social and equity implications of urban technologies and innovations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Environmental Impact Assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced sensors and data analytics to optimize energy use and reduce carbon emissions in urban energy systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
