&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topics covered:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Papers are solicited with the topics of interest including, but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sustainability performance measures/metrics and their interrelationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tools/models for sustainability performance measurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parametric models and platforms for planning, design &amp; visualization of sustainable cities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role of hyper-complex systems engineering and systems integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Considerations for retrofitting and new acquisitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key technology trends/drivers (e.g. IoT, autonomous vehicles) and their impacts including societal implications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Human factors and societal considerations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart cities and their supporting infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Low-carbon economy and society (including lifestyle)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New urban form for future cities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community resilience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Novel infrastructure systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Human-infrastructure interaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liveable future cities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vulnerability and risk assessment, and mitigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Authors should indicate in their cover letter the ways that their papers fit the SI by relating clearly to the specified topics and keywords. Authors failing to do so may have their manuscripts returned for amendments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We hope that this can be checked by the Editorial Office before the manuscripts are assigned to an Editor.&lt;/p&gt;
