&lt;p&gt;How to effectively reduce carbon footprint during human activities and industrial operations is still one of the biggest challenges. Carbon storage and utilization in the subsurface is a key to tackle this challenge, especially fossil energy is still dominating the energy field. Carbon dioxide storage and utilization is likely to be widely deployed in the coming decades due to major climate and economic drivers, and hence hundreds of millions or billions of tons of Carbon dioxide may be stored annually. The Special Issue focuses on the recent advances in carbon storage and utilization.&lt;/p&gt;
