&lt;p&gt;Digital disruption has affected many areas of the world and society (Nyagadza, 2022). The influence of digital industry and the digitalization of enterprises on business innovation has become a major research topic (Li et al., 2023). Interest in information and communication technology (ICT) and its application in emerging economies has increased in recent years (Tongkaw, 2013). Technological innovation has had benefits that vary across geographies and social classes (Phillips &amp; Linstone, 2016). Thus, it is essential to consider the socioeconomic implications of digitalization in emerging countries.&lt;/p&gt;
