&lt;p&gt;The focus and scope of the SI including possible research questions in following topics which are illustrative but not exhaustive, as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to engage stakeholders from a wide range of complex systems at macro, meso, and micro levels for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations, ranging from financial, market, human resource, emergency/risk management, logistics systems to other associated systems?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to deploy existing or develop new technologies and innovation processes to promote AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to create an ecosystem and business models involving multiple industries such as microchip manufacturing, service, transport, and the like for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to manage and develop AI-driven applications for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What kind of AI-driven interconnection for seamless communication is needed for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to promote AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations (e.g., enhancing information transparency, and knowledge sharing and transferring for decision-making etc)?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to improve simulation and visualization of AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations? What kind of technical innovation or technical aids do we need?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What type of decision-making (e.g., decentralized decision-making) can facilitate AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What is the role of AI-driven transport in enabling physical flows for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to use IoT to monitor and control operating systems for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What are the impacts of sophisticated digital technologies (e.g., blockchain and other disruptive technologies) on AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guest editors:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tachia CHIN (Lead Guest Editor)&lt;br&gt;School of Management, Zhejiang University of Technology, China&lt;br&gt;tachiachin@zjut.edu.cn&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Shouyang WANG&lt;br&gt;Center for Forecasting Science of Chinese Academy of Sciences, University of Chinese Academy of Sciences, China&lt;br&gt;sywang@amss.ac.cn&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;T.C.E. CHENG&lt;br&gt;Department of Logistics and Maritime Studies, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hong Kong&lt;br&gt;edwin.cheng@polyu.edu.hk&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Chun-Hsien WANG&lt;br&gt;College of Management, Chiayi University, Taiwan&lt;br&gt;chwang@mail.ncyu.edu.tw&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mei-Chih HU&lt;br&gt;Institute of Technology Management, Tsing Hua University, Taiwan&lt;br&gt;mchu@mx.nthu.edu.tw&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The astounding progress of artificial intelligence (AI) like the advent of ChatGPT is facilitating and stimulating the integration of AI and human intelligence (HI) to realize technological forecasting and assessment in many industries and domains as combining AI algorithms with human actors for decision-making enables organizations to be more agile and adaptive to changing conditions (Dubey et al., 2022; Chin et al., 2022; Cui et al., 2021; Hu et al., 2017). Given the integration of AI and HI helps optimize time-intensive processes, abate decision biases as well as minimize systemic risks in sophisticated activities, many humanitarian organizations and governments have applied it to better forecast and evaluate the efficiency, effectiveness, and transparency of complex humanitarian aid operations that affect the life or death of people in need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, given the hybrid application of AI and HI in the humanitarian sector is a nascent phenomenon, quite a few debates remain. For instance, some scholars advocate that AI cannot completely replace HI because the former lacks the flexibility and creativity that is so desperately needed in the humanitarian sector (Guss and Dorner, 2017). In contrast, some argue that AI with its unique machine learning attribute can synthesize the wisdom of a wider range of stakeholders than HI and thus should play a dominant role in humanitarian aid operations involving rich data from numerous stakeholders (George, 2017). Considering these controversies, there exist huge challenges and unanswered questions about whether and how the integration of AI-HI can be applied in humanitarian aid operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to the to the United Nations’ Global Humanitarian Review 2022, extreme poverty is rising, climate change is worsening, and millions of people are confronted with acute food insecurity. In 2023, a series of devastating earthquakes hitting Turkey and Syria have just drawn the world’s great attention. These incidents signal the growing need for humanitarian aids across borders. However, as discussed above, on the one hand, AI may be ideal for handling highly repetitive and precise tasks, but some complex tasks still need to be performed by HI, such as those intertwined with socio-psychological concerns, e.g., critical thinking, ethics, and cultural values. On the other hand, AI keeps evolving and may eventually become a counterpart of the human brain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The challenges and paradoxes addressed above not only imply some barriers to the success but also plenty of new opportunities in integrating AI and HI to optimize cross-border relief operations. Without doubt, it is imperative to fill the research gap. In response, given the infancy of relevant research, we organize this Special Issue (SI) to enrich this novel field of research that associates AI-HI integration with social, environmental, technological, and humane progress in the humanitarian sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome and invite conceptual and empirical studies based on a multitude of methods that address the representative topics outlined below. We particularly welcome cross-country empirical studies and encourage novel and innovative methodologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topics:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to engage stakeholders from a wide range of complex systems at macro, meso, and micro levels for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations, ranging from financial, market, human resource, emergency/risk management, logistics systems to other associated systems?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to deploy existing or develop new technologies and innovation processes to promote AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to create an ecosystem and business models involving multiple industries such as microchip manufacturing, service, transport, and the like for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to manage and develop AI-driven applications for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• What kind of AI-driven interconnection for seamless communication is needed for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to promote AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations (e.g., enhancing information transparency, and knowledge sharing and transferring for decision-making etc)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to improve simulation and visualization of AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations? What kind of technical innovation or technical aids do we need?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• What type of decision-making (e.g., decentralized decision-making) can facilitate AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• What is the role of AI-driven transport in enabling physical flows for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• How to use IoT to monitor and control operating systems for AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• What are the impacts of sophisticated digital technologies (e.g., blockchain and other disruptive technologies) on AI-HI integration in humanitarian aid operations?&lt;/p&gt;
