&lt;p&gt;The astounding progress of artificial intelligence (AI) like the advent of ChatGPT is facilitating and stimulating the integration of AI and human intelligence (HI) to realize technological forecasting and assessment in many industries and domains as combining AI algorithms with human actors for decision-making enables organizations to be more agile and adaptive to changing conditions (Dubey et al., 2022; Chin et al., 2022; Cui et al., 2021; Hu et al., 2017). Given the integration of AI and HI helps optimize time-intensive processes, abate decision biases as well as minimize systemic risks in sophisticated activities, many humanitarian organizations and governments have applied it to better forecast and evaluate the efficiency, effectiveness, and transparency of complex humanitarian aid operations that affect the life or death of people in need.&lt;/p&gt;
