&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In recent years, the vital role of digital transformation has been recognized in the creation, success and sustainability of firms (Dongquin et al.; 2022; Baiyere et al., 2020; Davison and Tarafdar, 2018; Dwivedi et al., 2020; Kraus et al., 2022; Sebastian et al., 2017; Wessel et al., 2021; Wimelius et al., 2021). Organizations face a variety of strategic challenges related to innovation, digital marketing, business intelligence, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The business landscape is becoming more complex for small businesses due to the challenges of a global marketplace, swiftly changing technology, aggregated purchasing and competitive pressures. A growing number of businesses are negotiating this complexity by joining or forming networks to tackle the scale and capability limits inherent in operating a small business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Digital networks are a largely underdeveloped resource in the business world and a strategic choice when businesses face complex issues in the domestic, interstate and international marketplace (Dongquin et al., 2022; Zhu et al., 2022). The logic is compelling - building on the strengths of others while nurturing one's own business strengths can help gain competitive advantage (Kraus et al., 2022; Dwivedi et al., 2020) .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a large number of studies that analyze the relationship between business intelligence systems and innovation in organizations (Zhu et al., 2022; Wimelius et al., 2021). The importance of digital transformation in decision-making lies in the possibility of decreasing uncertainty, thereby contributing to a more rational decision-making process. Digital transformation has a direct effect on performance in general and on innovation in particular (Alalwan et al., 2021; Baiyere et al., 2020; Davison and Tarafdar, 2018; Majchrzak et al., 2016; Sebastian et al., 2017).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Submissions can be from different theoretical perspectives and can use different empirical methods, large scale survey work and archival databases, but must constitute new ideas, that genuinely advance existing debates.&lt;/p&gt;
