&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This special issue may include, but is not limited to, the following topics relevant to Digital Economy-Oriented Artificial Intelligence Technologies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Low-carbon training of AI big models;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Theories and methods for AI-driven digital economy;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. Construction technologies of smart cities, smart medical, intelligent transportation, and other intelligent fields;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4. Intelligent prediction of financial risk, climate change, and Environmental Social and Governance (ESG) in the era of the digital economy;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5. Big data intelligence, approximation, and green computing technologies for specific economic fields;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;6. Intelligent data management and processing methodologies to support digital economy development;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7. Intelligent collaborative scheduling of computing power for the new economic paradigm;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8. AI chip-based computing power improvement strategies for computational economy;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;9. AI technologies to promote both digital industrialization and industrial digitization;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;10. Other AI theories, methods, and algorithms related to the digital economy.&lt;/p&gt;
