&lt;p&gt;The concept of industry 4.0 is based on the ideas of smart factory, characterized by production systems completely interconnected from the inside world to the outside world, automation and robotics, the optimization of productivity, smart equipment and collaborative robots, the design of modular, more flexible, reconfigurable and adaptable production lines, reducing waste and energy consumption, the prevention of errors and delays, enhanced logistics and inventory management, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This special issue is dedicated to contributions of artificial intelligence, data science, modelling techniques and heuristics to the decision aid and optimization in industry 4.0, automation and robotics in machining and assembly environments.&lt;/p&gt;
