&lt;p&gt;The maritime industry is facing increasing pressure to improve efficiency in the face of growing global demand and increasingly complex operating environments. One promising area is the development of advanced machine learning to optimize various aspects of maritime operations. However, existing approaches mainly focus on classical machine learning. Therefore, the advancement of machine learning, such as deep learning, learning on graphs, deep reinforcement learning, and automatic machine learning for the maritime industry still needs to be sufficiently investigated and benchmarked. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Advanced learning algorithms facilitate intelligent decision-making in maritime applications, such as vessel trajectory mining, maritime traffic flow forecasting, shipping market modeling, etc. Moreover, maritime data are usually time-varying, high-dimensional, imperfect, non-Euclidean, or noisy, which challenges developing advanced learning algorithms. This special issue aims to bring together the recent developments of advanced machine learning for the maritime industry. Furthermore, this special issue encourages maritime researchers to provide publicized datasets. Original contributions and comparative studies among the advanced machine learning methods are welcome, with a comprehensive literature review and fair comparative results.&lt;/p&gt;
