&lt;p&gt;With the development of modern manufacturing technologies, intelligent manufacturing is contributed to all the operations for manufacturing, assembling, and disassembling of tasks and products for controlling and monitoring these operations using industrial informatics and Industry 4.0 or 5.0. In addition, sustainable development goals enforce industrial practitioners to optimize the reduction of waste and energy while focusing on wealth generation and job creation for society. Green manufacturing system involves various techniques and practices to make the operations for manufacturing, assembling, and disassembling of tasks and products environmentally and socially friendlier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generally, solving manufacturing problems are computationally extensive and this fact highlights the role of innovative heuristics and metaheuristics in addressing the complexity of products and the scheduling of machines. This proposed special issue aims to publish high-quality research papers on the application of innovative heuristics and metaheuristics for solving intelligent and green manufacturing systems.&lt;/p&gt;
