&lt;p&gt;Maintenance Engineering, Asset and Operations Management have been among the strongest beneficiaries of applied AI. The emergence of Cyber-Physical Systems, the Internet of Things, Digital Twins, and the expansion of Data Modelling, Management, Processing, and Communication capabilities across the Edge to Cloud Continuum, further empower industrial AI. Such advancements make it affordable to expand AI opportunities into low-cost solutions, thus widening their adoption base. This issue aims to promote the latest advances in the field enabling maintenance engineering, asset and operations management functions to maximise the value delivered by engineering assets in close alignment with their operating technical, infrastructure, and business environments.&lt;/p&gt;
