&lt;p&gt;The metaverse is a cosmos that combines physical reality with digital virtuality in a continualmulti-user environment. Metaverse is built on the convergence of technologies, such as virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR), mixed reality (MR), and extended reality (XR), enabling multimodal interactions with virtual environments, digital elements, and people. A metaverse allows people to live and work in a virtual place (Pamucar et al., 2022; Hwang and Chien, 2022). In the metaverse space, people can engage in social activities such as discussing an issue, collaborating on a project, playing games, and learning from experiencing or solving some problems (Bourlakis et al., 2009; Jovanović &amp; Milosavljević, 2022; Park &amp; Kim, 2022). One's partners or friends in the metaverse could be real persons or virtual characters (Díaz et al., 2020; Kye et al., 2021). Moreover, there can be various kinds of activities or events in the metaverse just&lt;br&gt;as in the real world, such as economic activities, political events, and natural disasters (Davis et al., 2009; Díaz et al., 2020). In such a virtual world, the only limitation is people's imagination. Moreover, with the lifelogging function, the details of life in the metaverse can be fully recorded (Thawonmas &amp; Fukumoto, 2011).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guest editors:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Assoc. Prof. Muhammet Deveci&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;National Defence University, Turkey&lt;br&gt;University College London, U.K.&lt;br&gt;Email: muhammetdeveci@gmail.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Prof. Dursun Delen&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Oklahoma State University, USA&lt;br&gt;Email: dursun.delen@okstate.edu&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Assoc. Prof. Dragan Pamucar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;University of Belgrade, Serbia&lt;br&gt;Email: dpamucar@gmail.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Prof. Aos Alaa Zaidan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;SP Jain School of Global Management, Lidcombe, Australia&lt;br&gt;Email: aws.alaa@gmail.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Assoc. Prof. Ilgin Gokasar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bogazici University, Turkey&lt;br&gt;Email: ilgin.gokasar@boun.edu.tr&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. Prof. Mario Köppen&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Kyushu Institute of Technology, Iizuka, Japan&lt;br&gt;Email: mkoeppen@ieee.org&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moreover, artificial intelligence (AI) is a required technology to enable the world of the metaverse to work following the rules defined by the creator. From this framework, it can be seen that an AR or VR system could be part of the metaverse for presenting the virtual content; on the other hand, the metaverse could contain AR or VR elements plus other required elements (Hwang and Chen, SI Proposal Form2022). Moreover, decentralized technologies (e.g., blockchains) are required to ensure that economic activities can be safely conducted and that personal property and logs in the metaverse will not be modified by others (Min and Cai, 2022).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Decision support system (DSS)-based approaches using soft computing techniques are pivotal factors in identifying business trends and emerging technologies. These progressive trends can help companies/researchers to identify connections between innovation and sustainability aimed at integrating Soft computing techniques into decision-making processes for the achievement of better applications in virtual worlds like a metaverse. With soft computing techniques, one can examine each metaverse area and make decisions most effectively and efficiently. Current AI tools are advanced enough to be integrated into decision support systems for metaverse applications and influence decision-making processes in significant ways. Building virtual worlds in the metaverse may benefit from a thorough investigation of AI-based techniques related to various technical aspects, such as natural language processing, machine vision, blockchain, networking, digital twins, and neural interface. To guarantee system interoperability, protect privacy, and integrate various services, this combination may have social effects and explore opportunities for government, business, and academic collaboration. Hence, It is necessary to investigate the stateof-the-art AI-based techniques, such as traditional ML algorithms and DL architectures, used to power various metaverse-enabling technologies: neural interface, natural language processing, machine vision, blockchain, networking, and digital twins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This special issue is open to new articles on soft computing-based models for metaverse applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Topics Covered&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The list of potential topics included, but is not limited to applications of soft computing and related&lt;br&gt;intelligent methodologies to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Decision Support Systems in metaverse platforms&lt;br&gt;Design and implementation issues in the metaverse&lt;br&gt;Metaverse metaheuristics installation and application&lt;br&gt;Applications of artificial intelligence in the metaverse&lt;br&gt;Interconnectivity between the metaverse and the real world&lt;br&gt;Security and privacy issues on the metaverse&lt;br&gt;Principal technical aspects in the metaverse (such as NLP, machine vision, blockchain,&lt;br&gt;networking, DT, neural interface, and many application )&lt;br&gt;Prominent metaverse projects that used AI to improve service quality and encompass the&lt;br&gt;metaverse's ecosystem&lt;br&gt;Different metaverse enabling technologies: natural language processing, machine vision,&lt;br&gt;blockchain, networking, digital twins, and neural interface&lt;br&gt;Smart NFT and other metaverse-based blockchain frameworks&lt;br&gt;Prospects and challenges of the Metaverse application&lt;br&gt;Compute and data-intensive networks in the metaverse&lt;br&gt;Fuzzy systems for metaverse applications&lt;br&gt;Metaverse applications using multi-criteria decision-making approaches&lt;br&gt;Traffic safety implementations in the metaverse.&lt;/p&gt;
