&lt;p&gt;The rapid rise of the Internet and digital economy has propelled human society into the era of big data. This term refers to descriptions of massive, complex, and real-time data, including commercial big data, medical big data, industrial big data, agricultural big data, &lt;em&gt;et cetera&lt;/em&gt;. Big data analytics requires sophisticated management analysis and processing techniques to extract insights from the sources. Both data analytics and high-performance computing have made significant progress in society –changing AI applications in many areas. A great success is learning from massive amounts of data in real time to identify newly emerging unknown patterns quickly. Incomplete, inaccurate, or inconsistent data still pose a challenge for all types of data analytics. Data analysis must combine the best qualities of the human mind and computers in order to construct relevant and reliable knowledge and use it as part of a decision-making process. There are many challenges and open research problems to be explored, as well as many issues to be addressed, for knowledge-based data analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
