&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special issue information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this Special Issue, solutions to these demanding problems will be explored that exploit the TAO theories of three-way decision and granular computing. They are human-inspired computational methods and techniques that respectively deal with thinking, problem-solving, and information-processing in threes, and at multiple levels of granularity. High-impact articles with applications ranging from feature selection to stock investments, infrastructure development, or medical diagnosis, as well as dedicated Special Issues in top journals, prove that their practical dimension is undeniable. Compared with traditional data analysis techniques, these theories consider the different granular structures of data, triadic methods, and the uncertainty inherited in human cognition. They help us to effectively reduce both computational costs and risk in many decision-making problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Researchers are invited to contribute to this Special Issue with an applicable perspective of these theories towards knowledge enhanced data analytics under uncertainty. The Special Issue focuses on practical problems regarding the effective use of prior knowledge both to aid decision-making, to enhance data analytics for autonomous decision-making, and to explain decision-making results. Consequently, this Special Issue aims at bringing together both researchers from academia and practitioners from industry to discuss the latest progress and launch new research topics pertaining to applications of these thriving areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this Special Issue, we will consider submissions that deal with theories and applications of three-way decision and granular computing with &lt;a name="OLE_LINK3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;data analysis under uncertainty. Articles that are not innovative enough in data analysis and/or applications will not be considered for publication in this Special Issue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The topics of interest include, but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.Three-way decision and granular computing-based knowledge enhanced data analytics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Knowledge-based granular data analytics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. Knowledge-based three-way data analytics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4.Three-way approximations of different types of fuzzy sets, including interval valued/linguistic assessments/fuzzy numbers/intuitionistic fuzzy sets/shadowed sets/hesitant fuzzy sets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5.Three-way decision and granular computing under incomplete hybrid data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;6.Three-way decision and granular computing under inconsistent multi-scale data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7. Cost-sensitive approximate learning under both qualitative and quantitative data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8.Three-way approximate attribute reduction and feature selection under multidimensional data&lt;a name="OLE_LINK6"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;9. Dynamic three-way approximation with real-time and uncertain data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;10. Sequential three-way decision under multilevel and multi-view granularity spaces&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;11. Multi-granulation three-way decision under multi-dimensional and multi-level data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;12. Three-way decision or three-way group decision under uncertain multi-attribute decision-making&lt;a name="OLE_LINK5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;13. Multi-attribute prediction approach under three-way decision with uncertain data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;14. Three-way recommendation using uncertain business data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;15. Three-way conflict analysis with uncertain conflict problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;16. Three-way concept learning with cognitive analytics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;17. Three-way enhanced technique under uncertain text data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18. Three-way cluster analysis under uncertain dynamic data&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;19. Three-way decision-based uncertain image processing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;20. Three-way decision in sentiment analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;21. Three-way hypotheses analysis and assessment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22. Three-way decision in knowledge management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;23. Three-way decision support systems and applications under environments&lt;/p&gt;
